-- Sun Hung Kai Properties, Cheung Kong, Nan Fung Market Homes, Standard Says
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-09-27T20:19:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/sun-hung-kai-properties-cheung-kong-nan-fung-market-homes-standard-says.html
Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd .
released prices for the first 28 free-standing houses at its
Valais development in Hong Kong’s Sheung Shui district, the
Standard reported today.  The developer set the average price of the houses at
HK$8,388 per square foot, with the cheapest units selling for a
total of HK$20.5 million, the Hong Kong-based English-language
newspaper said, citing Victor Lui, an executive director of the
developer’s real estate agency unit.    Cheung Kong  (Holdings) Ltd. put 288 additional apartments
and 14 houses in its Oceanaire project in Ma On Shan on sale at
an average of HK$6,811 per square foot and HK$8,353 per square
foot respectively, the Standard said.    Nan Fung Development Ltd. priced 30 apartments, mainly
studio units, in its Queen’s Cube project at an average of
HK$15,570 per square foot, the Standard said, citing company
Director Victor Mak.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
